<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="307" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1197,1618]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1377,1402]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Distribution.</emphasis>
From northern Africa (
<collectingCountry box="[623,729,1378,1402]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[741,826,1377,1402]" name="Tunisia" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[874,936,1377,1402]" name="Israel" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Israel</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[994,1095,1377,1402]" name="Palestine" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Palestine</collectingCountry>
and to the Arabian Peninsula (
<collectingCountry box="[159,232,1414,1438]" name="Oman" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Oman</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[243,494,1413,1438]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1197,1618]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1449,1474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Pollen hosts.</emphasis>
Oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName box="[533,716,1449,1474]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Zygophyllaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Zygophyllaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<number box="[730,758,1450,1474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="38.0">38</number>
of 
<number box="[801,829,1450,1474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="39.0">39</number>
pollen loads (
<number box="[997,1024,1450,1474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="11.0">11</number>
localities, 
<number box="[1153,1167,1449,1474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="5.0">5</number>
countries) consisted of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,330,1485,1510]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Zygophyllaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Zygophyllaceae</taxonomicName>
pollen, and large numbers of males and females of 
<taxonomicName box="[917,1036,1486,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[917,1036,1486,1509]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">H. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been observed on the flowers of 
<taxonomicName box="[186,414,1521,1546]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Zygophyllaceae" genus="Zygophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="album">
<emphasis box="[186,414,1521,1546]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Zygophyllum album</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[568,651,1521,1546]" name="Tunisia" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[672,789,1521,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 5. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1644,1666]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,483,1619]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,483,1619]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 5. 1 – 3: Sandy slope at the shore of a salt lake near Medenine in southern Tunisia (Fig. 1), where females of Hoplitis minima collected pollen on the flowers of Zygophyllum album (Fig. 2) and males of Hoplitis hartliebi patrolled flowers of Frankenia cf. laevis (Fig. 3). 4: Hoplitis minima, head of female. 5: Hoplitis jordanica, terga 4 – 7 of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229654/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
). One pollen load consisted of pollen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1284,1432,1521,1546]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Brassicaceae</taxonomicName>
, indicating that flowers of this plant family might occasionally be exploited as well.
</paragraph>
